        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:31PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northeast of Springfield, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lawrenceburg, Versailles, Ballard, Bondville, Seaville, Ashbrook,
Klondyke, Mckees Crossroads, Mcbrayer, and Duckers.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
